reviewText: Thanks to Mill Creek for creating this awesome 1st season set and Amazon for their awesome service I can finally say i own The orginal He-Man the complete 1st season!  I already own the later he-man cartoons from the 90s and beyond but i could never find the orginal cartoon sets anywhere that was very affordable for me, but 13 bucks for the complete 65 episode 1st season?!  That was a hell of a deal!  I was shocked to find that it even contained a episode guide and the discs all arrived mint and perfect. I have only watched a handful of episodes so far, but the video and audio look great to me, very colorful and crisp and the audio sounds great as well. I would recommend that if you love He-man just buy this fantastic set now and hope they will release season 2 soon.

reviewText: Those of you who don't appreciate this release should realize how grateful you should be that it's even available. There are other great 80's cartoons that have not even been released in North America at all (M.A.S.K., the entire JEM, Pole Position, Inhumanoids etc). You are getting the entire first season in one box (not multiple sets, that costs more - which I hate) and it's only $20.00? Bare bones or not, this is a bargain. We really need to appreciate that Mill Creek made a quality show like this, and their other releases so affordable. Enjoy.

reviewText: This is a good classic cartoon show. I love the colorful and old fashioned art style. It was one of the most popular Saturday Morning cartoons back in the 1980's.This show has good voice acting and good looking characters. My personal favorite characters are Battle Cat, Beast Man, Teela, and of course He-Man. The episodes are well written and I also like the moral segments at the end of each episode. If you're looking for a good classic 1980's cartoon show, then you should definitely check this one out.

reviewText: Unfortunately, I did not have a good experience with this set.  Disc 1 would not play on either my Blu-Ray or DVD player.  I looked at the discs and they were all very scratched up.  It doesn't help that Mill Creek puts their discs in paper sleeves rather than plastic trays like most companies, thus making them more likely to have scratches.  I returned the set and got another, but unfortunately had the same results with disc 1 not playing and plenty of scratches on all the discs.  Also, one of the plastic tabs that attempts to hold the paper sleeved DVDs in place was broken.  I just returned the replacement set for a refund rather than risk getting another bad set.

reviewText: I agree with most sentiments on here - the packaging, typical of Mill Creek, is pretty bad, considering that if you want to replace the default paper sleeves with something else, the case that houses the 8 dvd's is essentially useless. I wound up taking an empty 25 disc spindle and putting the He - Man dvd's in that just to make sure I wouldn't scratch the DVD's with the frequent removal of the dvd's from their cases.With that said, the picture quality and sound is surprisingly pretty good (albeit there are on average about 10 episodes crammed up per dvd). I have a Denon receiver, a Sony HD TV, and some old school SONY dvd players but the episodes on the series look pretty crisp. At the time, I got this set for just under 13 dollars and to be quite frank, having 65 episodes of the first season for that price is a steal. Mind you, I've never owned the sets made available by BCI, although I did check them out from the library at one point. BCI sets are packed with more features but the Mill Creek version definitely has some interesting add ons.As a person on a budget,  I do not mind missing out on some added features that were made available by the BCI sets and what mattered to me the most is that what I originally bought this set for, the 65 episodes, did not disappoint. This one of the most cherished animated series that I've ever watched (Gargoyles, Batman the Animated Series, Justice League, Transformers, Voltron, Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes, Scooby Doo, etc. being others) and as being a father of a 3 year old, this is definitely a series I would like to have my son watch. The fact that the violence is pretty minimal and that there's an importance piece of advice from He Man at the end of every episode (i.e. stealing, being cognizant of others, etc) is what makes this series ageless.

reviewText: I was so excited to get this DVD set for my son, who discovered He-Man on Qubo.  But the storage box it came in has me so disappointed I wish I'd waited to try and find it in some other format.  I'll end up having to try to go and find some multiple DVD storage case and buying it just for this set.  It came in an oversised DVD box.  Regularly DVDs are stuck on a peg that goes through the middle hole of the DVD to hold it safely in place.  Not these.  Each disc is in a black paper sleeve. A PAPER SLEEVE.  Really? That's how bootlegged DVDs come, not off the rack, publisher released ones.  And then the stack of sleeves just sits in the middle of the box.  It's an awful set up.the quality of the actual shows is fine, so that's why I gave it three stars.

reviewText: I honestly do not understand why this product is getting such low ratings.First off. Masters of the Universe was previously released by BCI. The first season was split in two volumes. The episodes are put in produciton order rather then story order. (for example 'Return of Orkos uncle' is set before 'Orkos Favorite Uncle'). These two dvd sets are now very pricy and hard to find.This Mill Creek version in my opinon is much better. (which is why I dont understand the low rattings). First off you get the FULL season in one box set. thats 65, count them 65, full episodes in one set! Not split up in two sets. plus its all for a rather good price here on Amazon. The storys are also put in story order not production order. so 'Dimond Ray of Dissaperance' the first episode put on the first disc is in fact the pilot episode. (thats why the story takes time to introduce the council of Evil). Just as here 'Orkos uncle' is placed before 'Return of Orkos Unlce" just as it should be.So in other words you get the full season all in order,  every episode, storys set in the correct cronilogical order, plus its all for a good price.I have only ONE complaint and one reason for with holding the fifth star. the packaging. The box set has a small box compartment with the dics placed in paper sleeves within. not the most effeciant of ways to have a series set. this is my only complaint.Everything else is top notch. so seriously people stop complaining and get this set while you still can!!!As for the story itself. He man and the Masters of the Universe is very much a part of my childhood. He-man with his friends Man-at-Arms, Teela, the Sorceress, Orko, and all the rest battle Skeltor, Evil-lyn, Beastman, and various other foes.this perhaps the preimer series for Filmation. even now after all this time this series still has its mark in history. its been made into a live aciton movie, its spawned two spin offs; one about She-ra one is the New Adventures, and it has been rebooted for a new generation in 2002. If your a fan of this series I would say get this set while you can.Top notch work from Mill creek. scoring higher then the previous volume.agian my only complaint is packaging, but everything else is good.
summary: Masters of the Universe Mill Creek.

reviewText: To me He-Man and the Masters of the Universe and Thundercats are basically the same thing, just different characters, and the fact that He-Man and the Masters of the Universe is much better and has a MUCH better variety of heroes and even better variety of villains compared to most action cartoons of the 80's and 90's. Skeletor was always kick-butt! I HIGHLY recommend this first season of He-Man and the Masters of the Universe, this is the only season I love, after this it just got old, it was the same thing over and over. This first season was absolutely fun though and a joy to watch, really cool and holds up even after all these years that have passed.He-Man and the Masters of the Universe: Season 1 ***** out of *****Violent Content: 3/10 - Action Violence.
summary: Even better than the similar Thundercats!
